  "texts": [
    "This step is crucial for identifying key topics that are widely shared among countries and distinguishing between questionable and reliable sources, enabling a coherent comparison.",
    "We recall that we limited our analysis to these countries due to the limited availability of News-Guard ratings within this specific subset of European countries.",
    "Next, we examine both commonalities and differences among countries in their online discussions of these topics, focusing on user engagement and consumption patterns.",
    "To compare the landscapes of public discourse in the selected countries, our initial step involves identifying common topics extensively discussed in all four countries and by both questionable and reliable sources.",
    "To this aim, we employ BERTopic [35] to perform topic modeling on the content produced by news outlets' accounts over three years (see Section Materials and methods for further details)."
  ]
}